      "post_content": "In theory, this is a good thing, as with land destruction decks you will have a dead card if you draw land destruction and A) They have so much land it won't matter or B) You have already destroyed all of their land.\n  \n   \nHowever in case A) you are already done for and case B) They are already done for. So it doesn't work.\n  \n   \nThe only niche this can fill is a card in a deck to deal with a specific annoying nonbasic.",
